ls- List directory contents
ls -l : Long listing format
ls -a	: Include hidden files
ls -lh	: -h  Human-readable sizes
ls -t  : Sort by modification time
ls -r  : Reverse order while sorting
ls -R   : List subdirectories recursively
ls -S   : Sort by file size
ls -1  : List one file per line
ls -d */	 : List directories themselves, not their contents
ls -F	 : Append indicator (one of */=@|) to entries
ls -l -a	: Using Multiple Options- ls-la, ls-ltr

Cd- Change the current directory
cd ..  : Move up one directory level
cd ~:   : Change to the home directory
cd -:  : Switch to the previous directory
cd /:  : Change to the root directory

pwd	Print the current working directory
pwd -L  : Display the logical current working directory
pwd -P  : Display the physical current working directory (without symbolic links)

